    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 🔍 Step 6 — SHAP Explainability + Fairness Analysis\n",
        "\n",
        "### SHAP Feature Importance\n",
        "**SHAP (SHapley Additive exPlanations)** tells us exactly which features drive each salary prediction. This is what HR professionals need — not just a number, but *why* that number.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Salary Fairness Analysis\n",
        "We calculate the **gender pay gap** and **location premium** across every job title. This is a legally required analysis in many countries and the #1 thing HR agencies ask for."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "st_yA5bvY-HN"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# ============================================================\n",
        "# CELL 7 | SHAP + FAIRNESS ANALYSIS + SALARY CALCULATOR\n",
        "# ============================================================\n",
        "\n",
        "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(20, 7))\n",
        "fig.suptitle('HR Salary Model — XGBoost Results', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')\n",
        "\n",
        "# ── Plot 1: Actual vs Predicted ──\n",
        "ax = axes[0]\n",
        "ax.scatter(y_test, xgb_pred, alpha=0.6, color='#6366F1',\n",
        "           edgecolors='white', s=60, linewidth=0.5)\n",
        "mn = min(y_test.min(), xgb_pred.min())\n",
        "mx = max(y_test.max(), xgb_pred.max())\n",
        "ax.plot([mn, mx], [mn, mx], 'r--', linewidth=2, label='Perfect prediction')\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel('Actual Salary ($)')\n",
        "ax.set_ylabel('Predicted Salary ($)')\n",
        "ax.set_title(f'Actual vs Predicted\\nR² = {r2_score(y_test, xgb_pred):.4f}',\n",
        "             fontweight='bold')\n",
        "ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(mticker.FuncFormatter(lambda x, _: f'${x/1000:.0f}K'))\n",
        "ax.yaxis.set_major_formatter(mticker.FuncFormatter(lambda x, _: f'${x/1000:.0f}K'))\n",
        "ax.legend()\n",
        "\n",
        "# ── Plot 2: SHAP Feature Importance ──\n",
        "ax = axes[1]\n",
        "explainer = shap.TreeExplainer(xgb)\n",
        "shap_vals  = explainer.shap_values(X_test)\n",
        "shap_df = pd.DataFrame({\n",
        "    'Feature'    : feature_cols,\n",
        "    'Importance' : np.abs(shap_vals).mean(axis=0)\n",
        "}).sort_values('Importance', ascending=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "colors = ['#EF4444' if v > shap_df['Importance'].median()\n",
        "          else '#93C5FD' for v in shap_df['Importance']]\n",
        "ax.barh(shap_df['Feature'], shap_df['Importance'],\n",
        "        color=colors, edgecolor='white')\n",
        "ax.set_title('SHAP Feature Importance\\n(Mean |SHAP value|)', fontweight='bold')\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel('Mean |SHAP Value|')\n",
        "\n",
        "# ── Plot 3: Gender Pay Gap ──\n",
        "ax = axes[2]\n",
        "gap_data = df.groupby(['Job_Title', 'Gender'])['Salary'].mean().unstack()\n",
        "gap_data['Gap_%'] = ((gap_data.get('Male', 0) - gap_data.get('Female', 0))\n",
        "                      / gap_data.get('Male', 1) * 100).round(1)\n",
        "gap_data = gap_data.sort_values('Gap_%', ascending=True)\n",
        "colors_gap = ['#10B981' if v <= 0 else '#EF4444' for v in gap_data['Gap_%']]\n",
        "bars = ax.barh(gap_data.index, gap_data['Gap_%'],\n",
        "               color=colors_gap, edgecolor='white')\n",
        "for bar, val in zip(bars, gap_data['Gap_%']):\n",
        "    ax.text(val + 0.1, bar.get_y() + bar.get_height()/2,\n",
        "            f'{val:+.1f}%', va='center', fontsize=9, fontweight='bold')\n",
        "ax.axvline(0, color='black', linewidth=1, linestyle='-')\n",
        "ax.set_title('Gender Pay Gap by Role\\n(+ = Male earns more)',\n",
        "             fontweight='bold')\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel('Pay Gap (%)')\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.savefig('model_results.png', dpi=150, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# ── Fairness Summary ──\n",
        "print(\"=\" * 55)\n",
        "print(\"⚖️   SALARY FAIRNESS REPORT\")\n",
        "print(\"=\" * 55)\n",
        "overall_gap = ((df[df['Gender']=='Male']['Salary'].mean() -\n",
        "                df[df['Gender']=='Female']['Salary'].mean()) /\n",
        "               df[df['Gender']=='Male']['Salary'].mean() * 100)\n",
        "print(f\"   Overall gender pay gap  : {overall_gap:+.1f}%\")\n",
        "print(f\"\\n   Avg salary by location:\")\n",
        "for loc, sal in df.groupby('Location')['Salary'].mean().items():\n",
        "    print(f\"   {loc:<12} : ${sal:,.0f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"\\n   Avg salary by education:\")\n",
        "for edu in ['High School', 'Bachelor', 'Master', 'PhD']:\n",
        "    sal = df[df['Education']==edu]['Salary'].mean()\n",
        "    print(f\"   {edu:<15} : ${sal:,.0f}\")\n",
        "print(\"=\" * 55)"
      ],
